register-view.requirements:
A username is valid, if:
- It starts with a letter
- it only contains characters, numbers or an underscore
- it is not shorter than 3 letters, not longer than 30 characters

A password is valid, if:
- it has 6 characters
- it contains at least one digit
- it contains at least one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter and one special character

experimentCreate.logicHint:
Subspace Logic consists of two parts
1. Subspaces: For example [0, 2, 4] describes all outliers of the subspace containing the columns with indices 0, 2 and 4
2. Operators: For example [0, 2] and [2, 3] describes all outliers in both the first and the second subspaces (available: and, or)

If you specify more than two subspaces, imagine parenthesis on the right side (right associativity)
So for example [0] and [1] and [2] is interpreted as "[0] and ([1] and [2])"
Note that writing parenthesis yourself is currently not supported 😕️

Some examples
[0, 1, 2] or [1, 2]
[0, 1]
[0, 1] and [1, 3] or [1, 32]
experimentCreate.paramHint:
empty field --> default value is used,
red border --> invalid input type,
blue border --> parameter is not optional and needs a value,
gray border --> type is allowed but can still be incorrect
